Java input and Output principles
  Charactestics of Java I/O :
    1. Read information from various sources- input direction
    2. Write information to various destinations - output direction
    3. Information is transferred through a series of interconnected streams (pipes)
  Streams are catagorized based on:
     1. The type of data that stream can carry, for eg text or binary.
     2. Direction of the stream -input/output.
     3. Type of the source or destination to which the stream is connected.
     4. Additional features, such as filtering or transfromation of data.
Note:- Sources and destinations could be Files, Network Sockets, Console, Memory etc.
